                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Maternity & Paternity Leave -->
                        <div
                            class="p-10 bg-gray-50 rounded-[40px] border border-gray-100"
                        >
                            <h3
                                class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1a1a2e] mb-6 flex items-center gap-3"
                            >
                                üë∂ Maternity & Paternity Leave
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                                When you take leave, your income may drop, but
                                your 3a protection doesn't have to. You have
                                three main options:
                            </p>
                            <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
                                    <span class="text-[#C41E3A] font-bold"
                                        >01</span
                                    >
                                    <span
                                        ><strong>Reduce Contributions:</strong> Temporarily
